Name: CVE-2018-19148
Description: Caddy through 0.11.0 sends incorrect certificates for certain invalid requests, making it easier for attackers to enumerate hostnames. Specifically, when unable to match a Host header with a vhost in its configuration, it serves the X.509 certificate for a randomly selected vhost in its configuration. Repeated requests (with a nonexistent hostname in the Host header) permit full enumeration of all certificates on the server. This generally permits an attacker to easily and accurately discover the existence of and relationships among hostnames that weren't meant to be public, though this information could likely have been discovered via other methods with additional effort.

Name: CVE-2018-19210

Name: CVE-2018-19211
Description: In ncurses 6.1, there is a NULL pointer dereference at function _nc_parse_entry in parse_entry.c that will lead to a denial of service attack. The product proceeds to the dereference code path even after a "dubious character `*' in name or alias field" detection.

Name: CVE-2018-19212
Description: In libwebm through 2018-10-03, there is an abort caused by libwebm::Webm2Pes::InitWebmParser() that will lead to a DoS attack.

Name: CVE-2018-19213
Description: Netwide Assembler (NASM) through 2.14rc16 has memory leaks that may lead to DoS, related to nasm_malloc in nasmlib/malloc.c.

Name: CVE-2018-19214
Description: Netwide Assembler (NASM) 2.14rc15 has a heap-based buffer over-read in expand_mmac_params in asm/preproc.c for insufficient input.

Name: CVE-2018-19215
Description: Netwide Assembler (NASM) 2.14rc16 has a heap-based buffer over-read in expand_mmac_params in asm/preproc.c for the special cases of the % and $ and ! characters.

Name: CVE-2018-19216
Description: Netwide Assembler (NASM) before 2.13.02 has a use-after-free in detoken at asm/preproc.c.

Name: CVE-2018-19217
Description: ** DISPUTED ** In ncurses, possibly a 6.x version, there is a NULL pointer dereference at the function _nc_name_match that will lead to a denial of service attack. NOTE: the original report stated version 6.1, but the issue did not reproduce for that version according to the maintainer or a reliable third-party.

Name: CVE-2018-19218
Description: In LibSass 3.5-stable, there is an illegal address access at Sass::Parser::parse_css_variable_value_token that will lead to a DoS attack.

Name: CVE-2018-19219
Description: In LibSass 3.5-stable, there is an illegal address access at Sass::Eval::operator that will lead to a DoS attack.

Name: CVE-2018-1922
Description: IBM DB2 for Linux, UNIX and Windows (includes DB2 Connect Server) 9.7, 10.1, 10.5, and 11.1 is affected by buffer overflow vulnerability that can potentially result in arbitrary code execution. IBM X-Force ID: 152858.

Name: CVE-2018-19220
Description: An issue was discovered in LAOBANCMS 2.0. It allows remote attackers to execute arbitrary PHP code via the host parameter to the install/ URI.

Name: CVE-2018-19221
Description: An issue was discovered in LAOBANCMS 2.0. It allows SQL Injection via the admin/login.php guanliyuan parameter.

Name: CVE-2018-19222
Description: An issue was discovered in LAOBANCMS 2.0. It allows a /install/mysql_hy.php?riqi=0&i=0 attack to reset the admin password, even if install.txt exists.

Name: CVE-2018-19223
Description: An issue was discovered in LAOBANCMS 2.0. It allows XSS via the first input field to the admin/type.php?id=1 URI.

Name: CVE-2018-19224
Description: An issue was discovered in LAOBANCMS 2.0. /admin/login.php allows spoofing of the id and guanliyuan cookies.

Name: CVE-2018-19225
Description: An issue was discovered in LAOBANCMS 2.0. admin/mima.php has CSRF.

Name: CVE-2018-19226
Description: An issue was discovered in LAOBANCMS 2.0. It allows remote attackers to list .txt files via a direct request for the /data/0/admin.txt URI.

Name: CVE-2018-19227
Description: An issue was discovered in LAOBANCMS 2.0. It allows XSS via the admin/liuyan.php neirong[] parameter.

Name: CVE-2018-19228
Description: An issue was discovered in LAOBANCMS 2.0. It allows arbitrary file deletion via ../ directory traversal in the admin/pic.php del parameter, as demonstrated by deleting install/install.txt to permit a reinstallation.

Name: CVE-2018-19229
Description: An issue was discovered in LAOBANCMS 2.0. It allows XSS via the admin/art.php?typeid=1 biaoti parameter.

Name: CVE-2018-1923
Description: IBM DB2 for Linux, UNIX and Windows (includes DB2 Connect Server) 9.7, 10.1, 10.5, and 11.1 is affected by buffer overflow vulnerability that can potentially result in arbitrary code execution. IBM X-Force ID: 152859.
